Definition 4.2.7. We now define $\Phi:\text{Ind}({\mathcal{C}(A_{\mathbb{R}})})\to\{\text{arcs with endpoints % in }\mathcal{E}_{A_{\mathbb{R}}}\}$. Let $M_{|a,b|}$ be an indecomposable in ${\mathcal{C}(A_{\mathbb{R}})}$. We will define $\overline{a}$ and $\overline{b}$ in $\mathcal{E}_{A_{\mathbb{R}}}$. First, $\overline{a}$. • If $a\in{\mathbb{R}}$ is neither a sink nor a source then $\overline{a}=(a,\varepsilon)$ where $\varepsilon=-$ if and only if $a\in|a,b|$. • If $a=-\infty=s_{m}$ then $\overline{a}=(|s_{m},s_{m+1}|,-)$. • If $-\infty<a=s_{m}$ and $a\in|a,b|$ then $\overline{a}=(|s_{m},s_{m+1}|,-)$. • If $-\infty<a=s_{m}$ and $a\notin|a,b|$ then $\overline{a}=(|s_{m-1},s_{m}|,+)$. Now, $\overline{b}$. • If $b\in{\mathbb{R}}$ is neither a sink nor a source then $\overline{b}=(b,\varepsilon)$ where $\varepsilon=+$ if and only if $b\in|a,b|$. • If $b=+\infty=s_{n}$ then $\overline{b}=(|s_{n-1},s_{n}|,+)$. • If $+\infty>b=s_{n}$ and $b\in|a,b|$ then $\overline{b}=(|s_{n-1},s_{n}|,+)$. • If $+\infty>b=s_{n}$ and $b\notin|a,b|$ then $\overline{b}=(|s_{n},s_{n+1}|,-)$.
